Project Title: SAIHV (Just An Intelligent Secure System)
Overview
SAIHV is a personal private wreckingball assembly approach to architectural framework designed for Transient, Stateless Intelligence. Unlike standard AI frameworks that rely on persistent state and bloated dependencies, SAIHV utilizes a "Gene Primitive" engine—deconstructing complex agentic tasks into atomic, base-level OS primitives.

Core Innovation

Gene Primitive Assembly: Logic is dynamically constructed at runtime to meet specific task requirements, rather than relying on pre-defined, monolithic frameworks.

Zero-Forensics Lifecycle: Every operation follows an ingestion-verification-erasure loop. Data is processed, cryptographically verified, and sanitized, leaving no persistent forensic footprint on local or cloud storage.

Ultra-Lean Footprint: The entire operational environment (system-of-record, sandbox logic, and autonomous controllers) resides in <183MB, enabling rapid deployment and portability.

Stateless Execution: By decoupling the execution environment from the storage layer, the system maintains a "Zero-Drift" posture, ensuring absolute operational security.

Status
Core architecture hardened and fully verified via cryptographic hashing. The system is ready for modular skill injection and agentic development.
